    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD represents a masterclass in lightweight engineering, powered by the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The drivetrain delivers seamless boost transitions through the rev range, paired with a tactile 5-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Its front-midship engine placement ensures a perfect 50:50 weight distribution, complemented by a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension for razor-sharp turn-in. This example is a well-sorted driver with consistent compression and a robust vacuum system. While showing minor cosmetic wear commensurate with its age, the chassis remains rigid and the mechanicals are dialed for performance.",
